<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 7:46PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of east central Madison
County through 815 PM CDT...
At 746 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
south of Kingston, moving southeast at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.
Locations in or near the path include...
Kingston...                       Weathers...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
